com.amplifyframework.auth

Interface AuthCategoryBehavior

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AuthCategory, AuthPlugin, AWSCognitoAuthPlugin

    public interface AuthCategoryBehavior
    Specifies the behavior for the Auth category.

            java.lang.String password,
            AuthSignUpOptions options,
            Consumer<AuthSignUpResult> onSuccess,

        Creates a new user account with the specified username and password. Can also pass in user attributes to associate with the user through the options object.
        Parameters:
        username - A login identifier e.g. `superdog22`; or an email/phone number, depending on configuration
        password - The user's password
        options - Advanced options such as additional attributes of the user or validation data
        onSuccess - Success callback
        onError - Error callback

        username - A login identifier e.g. `superdog22`; or an email/phone number, depending on configuration
        password - User's password for normal signup, null if custom auth or passwordless configurations are setup

        onSuccess - Success callback
        onError - Error callback

      • fetchAuthSession

        void fetchAuthSession(Consumer<AuthSession> onSuccess,
                      Consumer<AuthException> onError)
        Retrieve the user's current session information - by default just whether they are signed out or in. Depending on how a plugin implements this, the resulting AuthSession can also be cast to a type specific to that plugin which contains the various security tokens and other identifying information if you want to manually use them outside the plugin. Within Amplify this should not be needed as the other categories will automatically work as long as you are signed in.
        Parameters:
        onSuccess - Success callback
        onError - Error callback
